{
  "texts": [
    "We intend for our maxims to guide the factors to be considered in analyzing a conversation, rather than for them to serve as explicit design goals.",
    "Regarding the inability of current models to accurately interpret the submaxims, it's not currently clear how to mitigate this issue (it's possible that prompt design can help).",
    "Regardless, the fact remains that models are inherently less able to interpret some dimensions compared to others, posing various operationalization issues.",
    "A.1 Illustration of Quantity",
    "The first example (1) violates the sufficiency requirement, whereas the second example (2) violates the unnecessary information requirement."
